{# ---- What is a CSM? ---- #}

<section class="o-section">



  <div class="o-container o-container--lg">

<div class="c-section-header">
      <span class="c-section-header__kicker">{{ title }}</span>
      <h2 class="c-section-header__title">What is a Community Safety Manager?</h2>
      {# <p class="c-section-header__description">Our Community Safety Managers deliver practical support and coordinated safety initiatives at the heart of local communities.</p> #}
    </div>

    <div class="c-prose">

        <p>A Community Safety Manager works closely with local communities, individuals, partners and organisations to understand safety concerns, coordinate engagement activities and support collaborative solutions.</p>
        <p>Their role is to support communities, partners and organisations across the rail network with any railway safety concerns, engagement requests or partnership opportunities.</p>
    
        <h3>How can your local CSM help you?</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>School or youth engagement requests</li>
          <li>Local safety concerns (trespass, ASB, community impact)</li>
          <li>Partnership working with councils, BTP, charities or community groups</li>
          <li>Support with campaigns, events or outreach initiatives</li>
          <li>Guidance on rail safety messaging, resources and materials</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="o-stack">
        <a class="c-btn c-btn--primary" href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>
        <a class="c-btn c-btn--outline" href="/contact/#csm-finder-heading">Find your local Community Safety Manager</a>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

